==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒzɪt|-ɒzɪt]] While the stress falls on the first syllable in most English-speaking countries (ie COM-pos-ite), it seems that most Americans stress the second (ie com-POS-ite).

===Adjective===
'''composite'''
# made up of multiple [[components]]; [[compound]] or [[complex]]
#{{mathematics}} not [[prime]]; having [[factor]]s
#{{botany}} being a member of the [[Compositae]] family (now known as [[Asteraceae]])
#{{architecture}} being a mixture of [[Ionic]] and [[Corinthian]] [[style]]s
===Noun===
'''composite'''
# a [[mixture]] of different components
# a [[structural]] material that gains its [[strength]] from a combination of [[complementary]] materials
#{{botany}} a composite [[plant]] (belonging to the family ''[[Compositae]]'')
#{{mathematics}} a [[function]] of a function

